# CitationIQ — Cursor IDE Rules
# Full engineering context lives in CLAUDE.md. Key rules repeated here for Cursor:

## Project
B2B SaaS — AI visibility auditing for local businesses.
Stack: FastAPI + React + Supabase + Stripe. Deployed on Vercel.

## Hard Rules
- Business logic in `backend/services/` only. Routes are thin orchestrators.
- All AI API calls in `backend/services/ai_engines/` — one file per engine.
- All frontend fetch() calls in `frontend/src/services/` — never in components.
- Framer Motion for all animated UI elements.
- Import `settings` from `config.py`. Never call `os.getenv()` directly.

## Naming
- Routes: `backend/routes/<resource>.py`
- Services: `backend/services/<resource>_service.py`
- Models: `backend/models/<resource>.py`
- Frontend pages: `frontend/src/pages/<Page>.jsx`
- Frontend components: `frontend/src/components/<section>/<Component>.jsx`
